  "prompt": "Client / server architecture?",
  "response": "Client/Server Architecture is a computing model where tasks and resources are distributed between providers (servers) and requesters (clients). Here's a comprehensive overview:\n\n1. Basic Concept\n- Clients request services/resources\n- Servers provide services/resources\n- Communication happens over network\n\n2. Components\nClient Side:\n- User interface\n- Request generation\n- Data presentation\n- Limited processing\n\nServer Side:\n- Resource management\n- Data storage\n- Complex processing\n- Authentication\n- Response generation\n\n3. Communication Mechanisms\n- HTTP/HTTPS\n- TCP/IP\n- WebSockets\n- gRPC\n- REST APIs\n\n4. Types of Client/Server Models\n- 2-tier\n- 3-tier\n- N-tier\n- Thin client\n- Thick client\n\n5. Advantages\n- Centralized management\n- Scalability\n- Resource sharing\n- Enhanced security\n- Performance optimization\n\n6. Common Examples\n- Web applications\n- Email systems\n- Database systems\n- Cloud services\n- Enterprise software\n\n7. Technologies\n- Node.js\n- Apache\n- Nginx\n- Spring Boot\n- Flask\n- Django\n\n8. Security Considerations\n- Authentication\n- Encryption\n- Access control\n- Secure communication protocols\n\n9. Performance Strategies\n- Load balancing\n- Caching\n- Connection pooling\n- Asynchronous processing",
